<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">nmee's magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heimdall00>Heimdall00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(1/27/03 7:46:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What new AAs would you like to see??</span><hr size=1> Greater Mind1 and 2, at each lvl you get +1 spell slot. I am sure shamans and bards would LOVE that one.<br>
<br>
Elemental horsie, i want that too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caeld>Caeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(1/27/03 10:36:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What new AAs would you like to see??</span><hr size=1> ooh, I like the idea of an elemental horse heh. I'd also just rather see them fix the skills we have. I think burnout needs its refresh time taken way down. It doesn't do a whole lot (fancy looking though) and its over an hour refresh. The new summoned fear/dot thing sounds like it sucks. if it was still 10k dmg, that'd be one thing but i know they changed it. I'm not sure howver what they changed it to. Anyone know? If they took the fear out it may become useful. Servant of ro also needs change, everyone I talk to says its a waste. Sure its got a low recast time but if it never hits and when it does hit never does damage, why bother? i say fix these skills first, then worry about new ones.<br>
<br>
Caeld <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xoniker>Xoniker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/03 12:48:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What new AAs would you like to see??</span><hr size=1> Passive type pet enhancement AAs would be great.  Or an AA that allows our elementals to share our skills, such as landing crits if we have SCF, improved HP if we have ND, better dmg avoidence for CA etc.<br>
<br>
We have no way of (permanently) improving pets through AA.  For a class that is designed to do around 50% or more of it's damage from a pet, this just seems wrong.<br>
<br>
SCF3 for a wiz = 7% more to their total damage - passive.<br>
SCF3 for a mage = 7% more nuke damage, maybe 3 or 4% to total damage.<br>
<br>
I'd also like to seem an activated ability for casting similar to rabid bear.  Maybe 20% more damage, 20% less aggro, and 20% additional chance to crit for 2 min on a 1 hour timer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nanid>Nanid</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.scorpz.com/icq.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/03 4:12:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.scorpz.com/nanidezz.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What new AAs would you like to see??</span><hr size=1> I like the idea of passive pet advancement.. it would make epic pet more useful in 60's rather than chunk it away with the low level.... something like this which can only be learnt after hitting 61.<br>
<br>
Pet enchancement<br>
Lvl 1 -- 5% more hp,  5%more damage.<br>
Lvl 2 -- 7% more hp,   7%more damage.<br>
Lvl 3 -- 10% more hp,   10%more damage.<br>
Lvl 4 -- 14% more hp,   14%more damage.<br>
Lvl 5 -- 20% more hp, 20%more damage.<br>
<br>
It would be something like 4k hp Hits like 90 plus max.<br>
Ain't too bad eh?<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.scorpz.com/nanidez.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lobaner>Lobaner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/03 6:10:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What new AAs would you like to see??</span><hr size=1> I like the elemental improvement AAs, anything that demonstrates that the true power of magicians is invested in us!<br>
<br>
I do not like the idea of an elemental horse.  Those guys are spooky.  Have you tried looking into their eyes?  I mean really looking?  They are up to no good, and all you casters that bough them will really regret it someday.<br>
<br>
How about a sustain companion ability that takes hitpoints from the magician (not like you're really using them anyway) and gives them to their elemental companion (me).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Lobaner</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heimdall00>Heimdall00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/03 7:54:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What new AAs would you like to see??</span><hr size=1> Hmm, I like the idea of passive pet enchantment. How about this one: every lvl of ability gives pet extra lvl. That would take care of problems with epics in PoP. Probably would be overpowered though...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2806<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 1:19:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What new AAs would you like to see??</span><hr size=1> A second level of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Elemental Pact</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that entirely eliminates the need for malachite.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cydmab>Cydmab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 772<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 9:33:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What new AAs would you like to see??</span><hr size=1> Pet-mage arbitration: Splits the hps between pet and master equally. So If I have 80% of 5k hps life, and the pet has 25% of 4k life, I use the ability (with some refresh timer, say 36 minutes) and we both now have 2500 hps each.<br>
<br>
You could use it either to sacrifice your pet's life to save your own ass, or use it as a painful lay-on-hands type ability on your pet.<br>
<br>
I'm apprehensive of &quot;pet enhancement&quot; because I'm woried it'll be sorta mandatory and openended. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I'm kinda comfortable with the idea of no-more must have AA abilities.<br>
<br>
How about an ability that makes your pet go into a shortrun &quot;frenzy&quot; that is meaningful? Or one that summons an extra drake that spits out nukes that effect normal mobs? Or one that gives you an elemental illusion that has non-negligable benefits? <p>Master Cydmab Promethean<br>
Arch Convoker of Morell Thule<br>
Fury's Edge</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cydmab>Cydmab</A> at: 1/30/03 9:35:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xoniker>Xoniker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#333333>(2/1/03 6:26:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pet hold</span><hr size=1> Oh, and like Rasc said a while back.  I want TOTAL control of my pet with pet hold.<br>
<br>
Improved Pet Discipline: Passive (no more spam, please). This ability gives the owner complete control over their pets.  Pets will attack given target ONLY and ONLY when specifically told to do so, ignoring any and all other forms of aggro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mavermage>Mavermage</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 387<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 2:56:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/Maverness/fullsize/NewMaver.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet hold</span><hr size=1>  The elemental focusing and pet combat fury would be nice to have. I'd love to see mages get some ways to really improve our pets. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tuis>Tuis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 8:50:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.elp.rr.com/scythek/everquest/Tuis.JPG height=120 width=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What new AAs would you like to see??</span><hr size=1> What new AA?  NONE!  I have enough to try and get as it is!<br>
<br>
...oh all right...if this can't be an innate skill for our class, then maybe it could find its way as an AA.<br>
<br>
